.SH NAME
cert-dump - Fetch and display certificates for a host or PEM file(s)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcert dump [host:port|cert.pem]... [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch and display certificates for one or more targets.

.PP
Targets may be:
- A TLS endpoint in host:port form (e.g., example.com:443) — the peer chain is
  retrieved and displayed.
- A path to a PEM/DER certificate file — the certificate is displayed.

.PP
Use --leaf-only to print only the leaf certificate when connecting to a host.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for dump

.PP
\fB-l\fP, \fB--leaf-only\fP[=false]
	only display the leaf certificate

.PP
\fB-s\fP, \fB--show-hashes\fP[=false]
	show hashes of all certificates in the chain


